{"title":"Happiness Writes White","author":{"name":"Edward Hirsch"},"publishDate":"2011-04-14","lines":[{"line":"I am a piece of chalk","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"scrawling words on an empty blackboard.","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"I am a banner of smoke","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"that crosses the blue air and doesn’t dissolve.","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"I don’t believe that only sorrow","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"and misery can be written.","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"Happiness, too, can be precise:","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"Doctor, there’s a keen throbbing","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"on the left side of my chest","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"where my ribs are wrenched by joy.","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"Wings flutter in my shoulders","stanza":1,"number":11},{"line":"and blood courses through my body","stanza":1,"number":12},{"line":"like waves cresting on a choppy sea.","stanza":1,"number":13},{"line":"Look: the eyes blur with tears","stanza":1,"number":14},{"line":"and the tears clear.","stanza":1,"number":15},{"line":"My head is like skylight.","stanza":1,"number":16},{"line":"My heart is like dawn.","stanza":1,"number":17}]}